<br>
About 4 months ago, my old guild Mithril Tower was just starting to kill things in HoT.  It had been a long day, learning how to pull, multiple wipeouts..ect.  We had finally broke the 2 wurms in the pit, and had the wandering mobs timed, and was able to pull at our liesure when EW comes along to kill Doze.  Now, after all the crap that we had been thru, to now having it interrupted, needless to say I was pretty pissed.  Sure enough, as they were moving in, a wurm popped, and they promptly killed it.  And as luck would have it...dropped a chain shirt.  But here is the key...THEY GAVE IT TO US!  Did they have to...nope,  but they knew we were there, and even apologized for interrupting us.  That totally changed my attitude.  <br>
When they finished, on the way out..one of them argoed the ToV friendly drakes outside and caused a complete wipeout.  I started dragging thier corpses to the zone so they could have a faster recovery.  Why did I do this...because they apologized...hell they probably do not even remember that event..but I always will.<br>
<br>
Ya..I pay my $10 a month...but so does EVERYONE else..and I make sure I keep that in mind.  You are not playing a game where everything but you is a AI controlled pixel.<br>
<br>
Shanno Flybane<br>
